{{Quote|So you fly these things through the asteroid belt?''"<br />"''Along Lando's Folly, not through. Against the flow of the asteroids. We've got a couple of particularly nasty sections mapped out. You want to try?|[[Jaina Solo Fel|Jaina Solo]] and [[Lando Calrissian/Legends|Lando Calrissian]]|<ref name="VP" />}}
'''Lando's Folly''', also known as the '''Dubrillion asteroid belt''', was an [[Asteroid field/Legends|asteroid belt]] in the [[Dubrillion system/Legends|Dubrillion system]]. During [[Lando Calrissian/Legends|Lando's]] mining project in the [[Star system/Legends|system]], he used the belt to put pilots from around [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] to the test; a pilot wishing to "run the belt" would pilot a modified version of a [[TIE Advanced x1/Legends|TIE Advanced x1]] [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]] into the oncoming asteroid belt, with the goal of staying in as long as possible. The course was dominated by ''[[Belt-Runner I]]'', a space station built to oversee proceedings and to protect pilots using [[Repulsorlift/Legends|repulsor]] shielding. A leaderboard was posted in Lando's facility, showing the pilots with the longest times. Shortly before the [[Yuuzhan Vong]] [[Yuuzhan Vong War|invasion]] of [[New Republic/Legends|Republic]] space, the three Solo children participated in "running the belt," and later used Lando's Folly to escape an oncoming hoard of Yuuzhan Vong [[Yorik-et|Coralskippers]].

